# Summary

This directory contains the script to burn the image with a FAT format partition at the first partition and copy the kernel and u-boot boot script into the partition.  


# Usage

    sudo ./burn.sh device kernel

    device
        the device is usually /dev/sda, /dev/sdb or so. A device name refers to the entire disk.

    kernel
        the kernel you want to load

## Example

    sudo ./burn.sh /dev/sdb HD-Elastos


# Directory Hierarchy

boot.txt                   u-boot boot script
burn.sh                    the script to burn the image into sd card
kernel                     the kernel to load
u-boot-sunxi-with-spl.bin  the u-boot spl image
